trans-unit.source: List all of the operations on a template deployment.
trans-unit.target: List all of the operations on a template deployment.

trans-unit.source: See <link xlink:href="953bb73d-e38c-4c29-bd35-1b2d5b37c5ce#bk_common" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Common parameters and headers</link> for headers and parameters that are used by all requests related to template deployments.
trans-unit.target: See <link xlink:href="953bb73d-e38c-4c29-bd35-1b2d5b37c5ce#bk_common" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Common parameters and headers</link> for headers and parameters that are used by all requests related to template deployments.

trans-unit.source: Replace {resource-group-name} with the name of the resource group in which the resources are deployed.
trans-unit.target: Replace {resource-group-name} with the name of the resource group in which the resources are deployed.

trans-unit.source: Replace {deployment-name} with the name of the deployment.
trans-unit.target: Replace {deployment-name} with the name of the deployment.

trans-unit.source: $skiptoken is optional and is only used if a partial result is returned in a previous operation call.
trans-unit.target: $skiptoken is optional and is only used if a partial result is returned in a previous operation call.

trans-unit.source: If the response contains a <parameterReference>nextLink</parameterReference> element, the value of the <parameterReference>nextLink</parameterReference> element includes a $skiptoken parameter with a value that specifies the starting point in the collection of entities for the next GET operation.
trans-unit.target: If the response contains a <parameterReference>nextLink</parameterReference> element, the value of the <parameterReference>nextLink</parameterReference> element includes a $skiptoken parameter with a value that specifies the starting point in the collection of entities for the next GET operation.

trans-unit.source: The $skiptoken parameter must only be used on the URI contained in the value of the <parameterReference>nextLink</parameterReference> element.
trans-unit.target: The $skiptoken parameter must only be used on the URI contained in the value of the <parameterReference>nextLink</parameterReference> element.

trans-unit.source: $filter is optional and can be used to restrict the results based on the state of the operation.
trans-unit.target: $filter is optional and can be used to restrict the results based on the state of the operation.

trans-unit.source: For example, you can use <codeInline>$filter=provisioningState eq '{state}'</codeInline>.
trans-unit.target: For example, you can use <codeInline>$filter=provisioningState eq '{state}'</codeInline>.
